  "prompt": "When were cotton fibres first used?",
  "response": "Cotton fibers have a long history of use. Archaeological evidence indicates that cotton was used in textiles in ancient civilizations as early as 5,000 BC. The oldest known cotton fabric was found in the Indus Valley Civilization, which flourished around that time in what is now Pakistan and northwestern India. Cotton was also grown and used by ancient civilizations in Egypt, Peru, and China.",
